    "content_hash": "5e9fe336bf9c25e4",
    "department": "Design",
    "description": "Join us as one the early members of our Product Design team and help lay the foundational building blocks of the next generation of social apps.\n\nWe’re looking for a Staff Product Designer whose superpowers lie in interaction design, motion, and systems-level thinking.\n\nYou'll be a part of a small and versatile team, so be prepared for virtually no routine. This also means you’ll have the freedom, resources, and agility to create top-notch products.\n\nYour focus will be to architect core UX flows in our products: developing signature interactions that crack user behavior and clarify our complex spatial models and features.\n\nYou have a meticulous eye and strong design fundamentals; you’ll regularly zoom out to a bird’s eye view, ensuring that the pieces click together.\n\nWith your high-level vantage point, you’ll drive and maintain a flexible design system to support rapid iteration and prototyping.\n\nAt amo, we thrive in creative chaos but our UX needs to feel simple, intuitive, and emotionally resonant to the users around the world who love our products… especially because our ambition is to reach billions of them!\n\n\n\n\nWHAT THIS LOOKS LIKE DAY-TO-DAY\n\nCraft \u0026 Ownership\n\nYou’ll craft signature interaction patterns, infusing motion in places to disentangle sticky flows and breathe life into our products.\n\nYou'll embed yourself in our design team and continually evolve our best practices for translating feature concepts into scalable UX and beautiful interfaces.\n\nIteration \u0026 Deep Collaboration\n\nYour natural instinct is to make ideas tangible early in the process, using prototypes to quickly test big, ambitious product ideas.\n\nYou’ll act as a bridge between design and engineering and work across multiple platforms and surfaces (iOS, Android, web).\n\nArtistic Boldness\n\nOur code and our craft are inspired by art, fashion, and emerging technologies.\nWe break standards and we are bold, always pushing each other to find fresh takes on what we build.\n\nYou’ll fire up your creative instincts and contribute to our collective imagination.\n\n\n\n\nYOUR SKILLS \u0026 EXPERIENCE\n\n - Hands-on, and care deeply about your craft.\n\n - 8+ years of experience designing consumer application, product, or software, even better if you’ve worked on consumer social products.\n\n - Obsessive about small details and visual finesse; you sweat the 1px difference and care about every transition and haptic.\n\n - Mastery of cutting edge design and prototyping tools and an appetite to acquire new skills.\n\n - Curious, self-directed, and excited by the ambiguity of early product work.\n\n - Comfortable communicating and collaborating in English (our working language).\n   \n   \n   \n\n\nEVEN BETTER IF YOU...\n\n - Are passionate about social apps and believe the consumer space is broken and ripe for reinvention.\n\n - Have complementary skills like 3D and are eager to experiment with generative AI tools.\n\n - Have strong opinions on art, culture, and fashion trends.\n   \n   \n\n\nLIFE AT AMO\n\n\nTo ensure that everyone is set up for success within our way of working, we work together onsite 5 days a week.\n\n\n\n\nWe wanted to make sure coming to the office was as comfortable as possible for you:\n\n - We chose a location in central Paris, near Opera (Metro lines 3,8,9 and RER A).\n\n - We have a beautiful Parisian-style office with high ceilings, balconies, and huge windows. So a lot of natural light!\n\n\n\n\nBecause life outside of work should also be stress-free, we cover:\n\n - Health care (100% coverage).\n\n - Maternity Leave, Paternity Leave, Second Parent Leave (salary maintained at 100%).\n\n - Vacation days: 8-9 weeks (total) per year - (European summer? 🥹😎).\n   \n   - 5 weeks of paid time off (by the state);\n   \n   - 1-2 additional weeks (RTT, based on our company contract);\n   \n   - ~11 bank holidays.\n     \n     We shut down entirely twice a year, two weeks in summer and one week in winter to allow everyone to truly recharge and to avoid prolonged slowdowns (especially in the summer). These pauses are part of your total vacation time, giving everyone a real chance to unplug and recharge. No Slack, no email, no FOMO.\n     \n     \n     \n\nWe love the diverse perspectives we get from having people from all over the world join us (68% of our team is international), and so we of course support relocation to Paris with:\n\n - Help and sponsored visa process.\n\n - 1 month of Airbnb 100% covered by amo upon arrival.\n\n - Assistance from a trusted relocation agency to find your permanent home.\n\n - Help with french paperwork like opening a french social security account, tax forms, getting your carte vitale (free healthcare) and more.\n\n - French lessons to be fully set with your new Parisian life.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
    "is_active": true,
